---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy — ThinkMode+" description="ThinkMode+ Privacy Policy. Learn how we handle your data — spoiler: we collect almost none of it.">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="legal-page">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Last updated: June 13, 2026</p>

      <p>
        ThinkMode+ ("<strong>we</strong>," "<strong>us</strong>," or "<strong>our</strong>") operates the ThinkMode+ browser extension for Google Chrome and Microsoft Edge, as well as the website
        <a href="https://thinkmodeplus.com">thinkmodeplus.com</a> (collectively, the "<strong>Service</strong>"). This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, and the choices you have.
      </p>
      <p>
        By installing the extension or using our website you agree to the practices described in this policy. If you do not agree, please uninstall the extension and discontinue use of the website.
      </p>

      <!-- ────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>

      <h3>1.1 Information You Provide</h3>
      <p>
        When you create an account, you may provide us with an email address. We have not integrated any payments yet, and we do not collect payment information. In the future, when paid plans are introduced, payment information will be processed entirely by <strong>Dodo Payments</strong> — we will never see or store your full credit card number.
      </p>

      <h3>1.2 Extension Settings (Chrome Sync)</h3>
      <p>
        ThinkMode+ stores your extension preferences (such as which AI platforms are enabled and your preferred thinking mode) using the Chrome Storage Sync API. This data is tied to your browser profile and synced across your signed-in devices by Google. We do not transmit this data to our own servers.
      </p>

      <h3>1.3 What We Do <em>Not</em> Collect</h3>
      <p>We are committed to minimal data collection. ThinkMode+ does <strong>not</strong> collect:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your browsing history or the URLs you visit</li>
        <li>The content of your prompts, conversations, or AI responses (except when Precision Mode is enabled, in which case content is accessed client-side only — see Section 3.3)</li>
        <li>Personal data such as your name, phone number, or physical address</li>
        <li>Keystroke or mouse-tracking data</li>
        <li>Analytics or telemetry data from the extension itself</li>
      </ul>

      <!-- ────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <h2>2. How We Use Information</h2>
      <p>The limited information we do process is used exclusively to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Provide the Service</strong> — sync your extension settings across devices and authenticate your subscription status.</li>
        <li><strong>Process payments</strong> — in the future, to manage subscriptions, issue invoices, and handle billing through Dodo Payments.</li>
        <li><strong>Communicate with you</strong> — send transactional emails related to your account. We do not send marketing emails unless you explicitly opt in.</li>
        <li><strong>Improve the Service</strong> — diagnose technical issues and improve reliability. Any debugging data is aggregated and anonymized.</li>
        <li><strong>Comply with legal obligations</strong> — respond to lawful requests from authorities when required by applicable law.</li>
      </ul>

      <!-- ────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <h2>3. Third-Party Services</h2>

      <h3>3.1 Chrome Web Store / Edge Add-ons</h3>
      <p>
        ThinkMode+ is distributed through the <a href="https://chromewebstore.google.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Chrome Web Store</a> and the Microsoft Edge Add-ons store. When you install the extension, Google or Microsoft may collect data in accordance with their own privacy policies. We encourage you to review those policies independently.
      </p>

      <h3>3.2 Payment Processing</h3>
      <p>
        We do not currently process payments. In the future, subscription payments will be handled by Dodo Payments. We will receive only a tokenized reference and the status of your subscription — never your full card details.
      </p>

      <h3>3.3 AI Platforms</h3>
      <p>
        ThinkMode+ modifies the user interface of ChatGPT to enable extended thinking features. The extension does not intercept, read, or transmit any of your prompt or conversation data. Your interactions with the platform remain governed by their respective privacy policy.
      </p>
      <p>
        When the optional "Precision Mode" feature is enabled by the user, the extension intercepts outgoing conversation requests to ChatGPT on the user's local device solely to append a fixed system directive ("[System Directive: Think step-by-step. Verify factual claims before stating them. Prioritize absolute accuracy.]") to the user's message before it is sent. This interception occurs entirely client-side; no message content is read, stored, logged, or transmitted to ThinkMode+ servers. The interception is disabled when Precision Mode is toggled off. Users are in full control of this feature at all times.
      </p>
      
      <h3>3.4 Supabase (Authentication & Database)</h3>
      <p>
        ThinkMode+ uses Supabase (supabase.com) as its backend infrastructure for user authentication and subscription management. When you create an account or sign in, your email address and authentication credentials are processed by Supabase. Supabase stores your account information (email address, hashed password, and subscription status) on its servers. Supabase may process this data in multiple regions. Their privacy policy is available at https://supabase.com/privacy. We do not store your password — it is hashed by Supabase before storage. The Supabase anon/publishable key included in the extension is a non-secret client-side key that grants access only to public data and authenticated user-scoped data via Row Level Security policies.
      </p>

      <!-- ────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <h2>4. Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        The <a href="https://thinkmodeplus.com">thinkmodeplus.com</a> website uses only <strong>essential session cookies</strong> required to keep you signed in and maintain basic site functionality. We do not use advertising cookies, third-party tracking cookies, or analytics cookies.
      </p>
      <p>
        You may configure your browser to refuse cookies, but doing so may prevent you from signing in or managing your subscription on our website.
      </p>

      <!-- ────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <h2>5. Data Security</h2>
      <p>
        We implement industry-standard security measures to protect the limited data we handle, including HTTPS encryption for all web traffic, secure authentication tokens, and restricted access controls. However, no method of electronic transmission or storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you believe your account has been compromised, please contact us immediately at
        <a href="mailto:vypur24@gmail.com">vypur24@gmail.com</a>.
      </p>

      <!-- ────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
      <p>
        We retain your account information (email and subscription status) for as long as your account is active or as needed to provide the Service. If you cancel your subscription and request account deletion, we will remove your personal data within 30 days, except where we are required by law to retain it (for example, financial transaction records).
      </p>

      <!-- ────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <h2>7. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        ThinkMode+ is not directed at children under the age of 13 (or under 16 in the European Economic Area). We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us with personal data, please contact us at
        <a href="mailto:vypur24@gmail.com">vypur24@gmail.com</a> and we will promptly delete that information.
      </p>

      <!-- ────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <h2>8. Your Rights</h2>

      <h3>8.1 Rights for EU/EEA Users (GDPR)</h3>
      <p>If you are located in the European Union or European Economic Area, you have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Access</strong> the personal data we hold about you.</li>
        <li><strong>Rectify</strong> inaccurate or incomplete data.</li>
        <li><strong>Erase</strong> your personal data ("right to be forgotten").</li>
        <li><strong>Restrict</strong> or <strong>object to</strong> processing of your data.</li>
        <li><strong>Data portability</strong> — receive your data in a structured, machine-readable format.</li>
        <li><strong>Withdraw consent</strong> at any time where processing is based on consent.</li>
        <li><strong>Lodge a complaint</strong> with your local data protection authority.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>8.2 Rights for California Residents (CCPA)</h3>
      <p>If you are a California resident, you have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Know</strong> what personal information we collect, use, and disclose.</li>
        <li><strong>Delete</strong> your personal information, subject to certain exceptions.</li>
        <li><strong>Opt out</strong> of the sale of your personal information. Note: we do <strong>not</strong> sell your personal information.</li>
        <li><strong>Non-discrimination</strong> — exercise your rights without receiving discriminatory treatment.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at
        <a href="mailto:vypur24@gmail.com">vypur24@gmail.com</a>. We will respond to verified requests within the timeframes required by applicable law.
      </p>

      <!-- ────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <h2>9. International Data Transfers</h2>
      <p>
        Your information may be transferred to and processed in countries other than the country in which you reside. We ensure that appropriate safeguards are in place to protect your data in compliance with applicable data protection laws, including Standard Contractual Clauses where required.
      </p>

      <!-- ────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we make material changes, we will update the "Last updated" date at the top of this page and, where appropriate, notify you via the extension or email. Your continued use of the Service after any changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
      </p>

      <!-- ────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <h2>11. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:vypur24@gmail.com">vypur24@gmail.com</a></li>
        <li><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://thinkmodeplus.com">thinkmodeplus.com</a></li>
      </ul>

      <hr />
      <p>
        Thank you for trusting ThinkMode+. We believe privacy is a fundamental right, and we're committed to keeping your data yours.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
